Generic Search Go Pages Members Categories Quicklinks Events Generic Major Events & Festivals Generic *Please note: No pets are allowed at any major event or festival.* Generic September 19-20, 2025 Mount Dora Magic Bash Presented by the Mount Dora Area Chamber of Commerce, Prepare to be amazed at Mount Dora's Magic Bash, where world renowned magicians perform for all ages. Enjoy intimate magic shows, 2 magic shows in the park, strolling magicians at select restaurants and a family-friendly magic class. WHERE: Various locations in downtown Mount Dora TIME : Various show and class times CONTACT : Mount Dora Area Chamber of Commerce at 352-383-2165 Generic October 10-12, 2025 51st Annual Mount Dora Bicycle Festival The Mount Dora Bicycle Festival serves as ground zero for pedal power. Several hundred cyclists of varying skills are expected to take up the ride, and hundreds more will join the celebration. It is Florida’s oldest and largest bike festival. Details on https://www.cyclemountdora.com . The Mount Dora Bicycle Festival serves as ground zero for pedal power. Several hundred cyclists of varying skills are expected to take up the ride, and hundreds more will join the celebration. It is Florida’s oldest and largest bike festival. Details on https://www.cyclemountdora.com CONTACT : https://www.cyclemountdora.com Generic October 25-26, 2025 40th Annual Mount Dora Craft Fair A two-day event. Crafters line the streets of Downtown. This nationally ranked juried event continues to attract over 200,000 visitors and over 350 of the best crafters in the country. FREE event. WHERE: Downtown Mount Dora TIME: 9AM - 5PM CONTACT: Website www.MountDoraCraftFair.com ; Phone 352-217-8390 Generic November 1-2, 2025 31st Annual Mount Dora Plant and Garden Fair Vendors and nurseries from all over the state convene to sell a wide variety of Florida native and exotic plants as well as garden ware and arts & crafts. FREE event. Saturday & Sunday! WHERE: Downtown Mount Dora TIME: 9AM - 5PM CONTACT: Janet Gamache at janet.gamache@gmail.com or 352-217-8390 Generic November 15-17, 2025 Renninger's Antique Extravaganza An antique lover's dream! One of the largest gatherings of antique dealers in the south with over 1,500 dealers attending. Three times a year Renninger's hosts this Extravaganza in the show field, antique center and under the on-site pavilions...rain or shine!. WHERE : Renninger's Vintage Antique Center, 20651 US Hwy 441, Mount Dora TIME : 8AM - 5PM CONTACT : Twin Markets at 352-383-8393 or visit www.renningers.net Generic November 22, 2025 Annual Light Up Mount Dora The city comes alive when the Christmas lights are turned on in Elizabeth Evans Park, Sunset Park and Donnelley Park. Drone show, pictures with Santa, entertainment, food vendors, and fireworks. FREE event. WHERE : Downtown Mount Dora TIME : Starts at 6 PM CONTACT : City of Mount Dora Generic December 5, 2025 Annual Mount Dora Christmas Walk A family friendly street party in downtown Mount Dora featuring music, street entertainment, food vendors, toy vendors, shopping (shops open until 9:00 PM), Free pictures by the Christmas Tree with Santa! FREE event. . WHERE : Sunset Park, Downtown Mount Dora TIME : 6PM - 9 PM CONTACT : Mount Dora Area Chamber of Commerce 352-383-2165 Generic December 6, 2025 Mount Dora Christmas Parade An old-fashioned Christmas Parade through the streets of downtown Mount Dora where you'll enjoy floats, bands, dancers, candy and Santa. FREE event. WHERE : Donnelly Street TIME : 10AM CONTACT : Terry Askins at 352-551-0133 / Mount Dora Lions Club 352-449-8443 or email communications@mtdoralions.org Generic December 6, 2025 Christmas Lighted Boat Parade Come out and enjoy the 34th Annual Lighted Boat Christmas Parade on Lake Dora. The parade begins at the lighthouse on Grantham Pointe (Tremain St & Liberty Ave) and can be seen in various locations on the lake. Local boat owners compete for best in light show display and originality. If you are a local boat owner and would like to participate, reach out for more information. WHERE : Grantham Point /Light House/Lake Dora TIME : Starts at 6:30PM CONTACT : Rusty Anchor Boat Tours 352-383-3933 Generic December 13, 2025 Children's Christmas Snow in the Park Join us in Elizabeth Evans Park for a chance to go snow sledding (tubes provided) on 3 levels of hills. Donate a toy for local charities and receive a Fast Pass for sledding. Pictures with Santa, and holiday entertainment. NO PETS---NO GLASS. WHERE : 100 N. DONNELLY STREET Mount Dora FL 32757 (Elizabeth Evans Park) TIME : 3P M - 9PM CONTACT : The City of Mount Dora Generic December 13-14, 2025 Holiday Tour of Homes The 46th annual Holiday Tour of Homes, now sponsored by the GFWC Mount Dora Woman’s Club will feature six area homes, each offering their own unique style and special decorations. Tickets go on sale on November 1st on gfwcmdwc.com.  All proceeds from the 2025 tour will be donated to LovExtension (lovextension.com), a local volunteer-run 501(c)(3) non-profit organization providing nutritional, emotional, and social support to homebound elderly and disabled individuals. WHERE : Various locations, map provided TIME : 11 AM - 4PM CONTACT : GFWC Mount Dora Woman's Club at https://www.gfwcmdwc.com/ Generic December 20, 2025 Mount Dora 5K A portion of race proceeds help support Mount Dora High School FFA & Run 4 a Cause Foundation. WHERE : 530 N. Donnelly St., Mount Dora, FL TIME : Starts at 7:45AM CONTACT : Vicki Blate - 352-729-2150 Generic December 21, 2025 Mount Dora Half Marathon A single loop half marathon. The half marathon is a USATF Certified Course. WHERE : Elizabeth Evans Park, 100N Donnelly St, 100 N Donnelly St. TIME : Starts at 7am CONTACT : https://mountdorahalfmarathon.com/ or Vicki Blate - 352-729-2150 Generic December 31, 2025 New Year's Eve Celebration Ring in the New Year with live music, food & beverages and a spectacular fireworks display over Lake Dora at midnight. Presented by the City of Mount Dora & Pisces Rising. Free Event. VIP Tickets available for $150 per person. WHERE : Sunset Park TIME : 9PM - 12AM CONTACT : piscesrisingdining.com or call 352-385-2669 Generic January 10-11, 2026 Mount Dora Highwaymen Art Show, Sale, & Benefit Visitors can enjoy scenic renderings of Florida's landscape expressed in the Classic Highwaymen art style, Admission is FREE. WHERE : The Donnelly Park Pavillion TIME : 11 AM - 5PM CONTACT : Heron Cay B&B at (352) 383-4050 Generic January 16-18, 2026 Renninger's Antique Extravaganza An antique lover's dream! One of the largest gatherings of antique dealers in the south with over 800 dealers attending. Three times a year Renninger's hosts this Extravaganza in the show field, antique center and under the on-site pavilions...rain or shine!. WHERE : Renninger's Vintage Antique Center, 20651 US Hwy 441, Mount Dora TIME : 8AM - 5PM CONTACT : Twin Markets at 352-383-8393 or visit www.renningers.net Generic January 22-26, 2026 Florida Storytelling Festival The Florida Storytelling Festival is a premier storytelling event, known nationally for its unique combination of workshops, concerts, youthful voices and sense of community.  People come from across the state of Florida and beyond to explore and savor the art of storytelling. The festival officially kicks-off with a special Thursday afternoon welcome reception followed by an evening storytelling concert. Friday and Saturday offer opportunities to immerse yourself in workshops, storytelling concerts, story swaps, story slams and lots of informal gatherings. Our wonderful Story Store will offer a multitude of storytelling resources. WHERE : Lakeside Inn, 100 N. Alexander Street TIME : Times vary each day CONTACT : Visit 352-234-6422 or flstory.com/festival fsa@flstory.com Generic January 23-25, 2026 Central Florida Film Festival A fun filled three-day event at the state of the art Epic Theatre in Mount Dora. 176 screenings will be available; all genres and lengths. Networking opportunities, nightly mixers, panel discussions, informal talk backs, screenings and award show with special guest presenters. WHERE : Epic Theatre - 2300 Spring Harbo r Blvd., Mount Dora, FL TIME: Show and event times vary CONTACT : CENFLO Film Festival at 352-216-2716 or visit www.cenflo.us. Generic January 31-February 1, 2026 50th Annual Arts Festival This nationally ranked fine arts festival attracts approx. 300 artist vendors from all over the world. The fine arts are displayed throughout the downtown streets of Mount Dora, attracting hundreds of thousands of visitors. WHERE : Downtown Mount Dora TIME : SAT, 9AM - 4PM & SUN, 9AM - 4PM CONTACT : Mount Dora Center for the Arts at 352-383-0880 or visit www.MountDoraArtsFestival.org . Generic February 13-15, 2026 Jane Austen Festival A three-day event featuring exciting Regency Era workshops and fun; Stained Glass, Lawn Bowling, Hot Air Balloon Rides, Sketching, Paper Quilling, Bonnet & Turban making, Regency Dancing, Unkindest Cut of All (regency insults), a marketplace, boat trip, tea & crumpets and more! WHERE : Downtown Mount Dora TIME : C heck website for times CONTACT : janeaustenfest.com Generic February 13-15, 2026 Renninger's Antique Extravaganza An antique lover's dream! One of the largest gatherings of antique dealers in the south with over 1500 dealers attending. Three times a year Renninger's hosts this Extravaganza in the show field, antique center and under the on-site pavilions...rain or shine!. WHERE : Renninger's Vintage Antique Center, 20651 US Hwy 441, Mount Dora TIME : 8AM - 5PM CONTACT : Twin Markets at 352-383-8393 or visit www.renningers.net Generic February 20-22, 2026 Scottish Highland Festival Celebrate the Scottish Culture with Live music, Highland athletics, society tents, re-enactment camp, Pipes and Drums performances, Kid’s activities, food and merchandise vendors. Family friendly. WHERE : Donnelly Park / Elizabeth Evans Park - Mount Dora TIME : Sat, 10 AM - 7PM & Sun, 10AM - 5PM (Donnelly Park). Sat. & Sun. 10AM - 5PM (Elizabeth Evans Park) CONTACT : www.mountdorascot.com . Generic March 21-22, 2026 Mount Dora Spring Festival A two-day event.  Over 200 vendors displaying treasures on the downtown streets of Mount Dora. FREE event. WHERE : Downtown Mount Dora TIME : 9AM - 5PM CONTACT : Email visitmountdora@gmail.com or website www.mountdoraspringfest.com or via phone 352-217-8390 Generic March 29-30, 2026 72nd Annual Mount Dora Yacht Club Sailboat Regatta The oldest sailboat regatta in the state, a fun day for the whole family. Sit on the shore and watch these beautiful pieces of art coast through Lake Dora. WHERE : Lake Dora and connecting waterways TIME : Sat, 12PM–4:30PM, Sun, 10:30AM–4:30PM CONTACT : Call 352-516-4031 or visit mountdoraregatta.com Generic April 12, 2026 30th Annual Mount Dora Earth Day Music, exhibits, raffle and lots of fun. Let's celebrate our beautiful planet and figure out how we can do our part to help our environment! WHERE : Donnelly Park, Downtown Mount Dora TIME : 9AM - 3PM CONTACT : Visit mountdoraenvironment.org or call 352-988-4022 Generic April 25-26, 2026 11th Annual Mount Dora Blueberry Festival A celebration of the rapidly growing blueberry agriculture business in Central Florida. We highlight local blueberry farms and celebrate all things blueberry: pie, short cake, wine, liquor, beer, fresh berries, scones and much more! Over 100 vendors, live entertainment and kids activities. Free event, open to the public. WHERE : Donnelly Park, Downtown Mount Dora TIME : 9AM - 5PM CONTACT : Call 407-913-4140  or visit mountdorablueberryfestival.com Generic May 2, 2026 Mount Dora Taste and Craft Beer Fest A Chamber Annual Event . This year while you are enjoying our local restaurants as they showcase their favorite dishes, you will also be able to learn about and sample some of the most innovative Craft Beers from Central Florida’s Breweries. Tickets available at MountDora.com by early April WHERE : Sunset Park, Mount Dora TIME : 6PM - 10PM CONTACT : Mount Dora Area Chamber of Commerce at 352-383-2165 Generic July 3, 2026 Mount Dora Freedom on the Waterfront An old-fashioned celebration of Independence Day in Elizabeth Evans Park. Enjoy live music, Kid's Zone activities, food trucks, beverages, and fun for everyone. A family friendly event. The evening ends with a spectacular firework display over Lake Dora. Presented by and the City of Mount Dora. FREE event. WHERE : Elizabeth Evans Park TIME : 5PM - Fireworks at Dusk CONTACT: C hris Carson 352-735-7183 or e-mail carsonc@ci.mount-dora.fl.us. Generic July 4, 2026 Independance Day Parade Join us in downtown Mount Dora for a patriotic tribute parade celebrating our country's independence! The City of Mount Dora is seeking entries for the annual Independence Day Parade in beautiful downtown Mount Dora. The parade begins at the corner of Donnelly and 7th Avenue and runs to Charles Avenue. WHERE : Downtown Mount Dora TIME : 10AM - 11AM CONTACT : Chris Carson at the City of Mount Dora Parks and Recreation Department at 352-735-7183 or carsonc@ci.mount-dora.fl.us for application Generic August 8-9, 2026 Florida Highwaymen Art Show, Sale & Benefit Florida Highwaymen Art Show, Sale & Benefit presented by Heron Cay Bed & Breakfast Inn & Kelvin Hair, Son of Alfred Hair WHERE : Donnelly Park Pavilion (corner of 5th Avenue and Donnelly Street) TIME : 11AM - 5PM CONTACT Heron Cay Bed & Breakfast 352-383-4050 Generic Generic Building Business. Building Community.

With samplings of fabulous cuisine from our restaurants, coupled with tents serving superior craft beer, a fabulous evening it will be!  Tickets available at MountDora.com by early April. WHEN: May 2nd, 2026                      WHERE: Sunset Park and Downtown Mount Dora                         TIME: 6:00 to 10:00 PM Generic Mount Dora Magic Bash Join us for Two Days of Wonder, Whimsy and World-Class Magic, Right Here in Mount Dora! Step into a weekend of mind-blowing mystery and family-friendly fun as the most talented magicians from across Central Florida bring their best to the charming streets, stages, and shops of Mount Dora. Check back on mountdora.com for updates! WHEN: September 19 & 20, 2025                      WHERE: Downtown Mount Dora                         TIME: Varies Generic Mount Dora Christmas Walk A Chamber Annual Event, always the first Friday of December. Join us for a family friendly street party featuring music, & shopping (shops open until 9:00 PM). Don't forget to visit Sunset Park to enjoy the Main Street Leasing Christmas Tree! Free event, open to the public. While you are strolling around, make sure to visit the Mount Dora Boating Center & Marina and Holiday Greeting Card Lane, you will surely be in the holiday mood! WHEN:  December 5, 2025                 TIME:  6:00 - 9:00 PM Generic Building Business. Building Community.
